column10: Numerous fender benders here and many near misses (I can hear the screeching of brakes and crunching of cars from my house). I report each one I hear but no effort has been made by the City to make this intersection safer.; Additionally,,drivers,ignore,pedestrians,in,the,new,zebra,cross,walk,at,this,intersection.,Several,times,I,have,been,in,the,intersection,with,cars,stopped,in,one,direction,while,drives,on,the,other,side,pass,right,in,front,of,me.; Very,bad,lines,of,sight,cause,drivers,on,Luray,to,have,to,pull,out,on,to,Commonwealth,to,see.,Drivers,on,Commonwealth,routinely,speed,,especially,if,they,see,that,the,light,at,Braddock,has,turned,green.

I was on a run in the early evening of Sept. 22nd, and was coming down Newton Street when I saw a speeding car coming down E. Luray Ave. There are pets and children on E Luray Ave, and the driver showed no concern for the safety of others.

We have daily problems with cars speeding down E Luray ave between Commonwealth Ave and Mt. Vernon Ave as a cut through. Cars do not follow the speed limit. There have been numerous reports over the years of problems on this street.

This is a common occurrence at this intersection. Newton St. has a stop sign, but E. Luray Ave does not. It is difficult for pedestrians and children on bikes to be seen by oncoming traffic on E. Luray St.
Dump truck made a right turn when I was in the crosswalk.

Car ran the stop sign on Hancock. I was proceeding West on W. Luray and did not have a stop sign. The car hit me and kept going. It did not slow down and missed several pedestrians in the area. Police report was filed.

This morning as my son and his friends were waiting to cross east as they do each morning, a black porsche cayenne with a yellow "don't tread on me" license plate raced around the car that had stopped for them and nearly hit all three. I have a picture.
Black Porsche SUV with yellow license plate

I was at the corner of Commonwealth and Braddock road, wait s for the light to turn white for the pedestrians light.  Once the light was in my favor I wanted to cross to the other side of Commonwealth when cars started turning right on red.  Not 1 car but 4 cars just rolled through the turn but never let me access the crosswalk even though I had white pedestrian walk light in my favor.  I am 13 years old and was both scared and angry at these drivers who could care less about my safety or my dogâ€™s safety.
